
PneumoGAN: A Variant of Generative Adversarial Network for Pneumonia Detection

This project leverages a novel variant of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), designed to improve biomedical imaging accuracy in detecting pneumonia. PneumoGAN enhances pneumonia detection with an impressive accuracy rate of 94.99%, showcasing advancements in medical image analysis.

A. Project Details

1. Overview
PneumoGAN was developed to address challenges in medical image-based pneumonia diagnosis by improving model training using synthetic data generation. The project's success demonstrates the potential of GANs in healthcare applications.

2. Implementation
The project includes:
- Data preprocessing and augmentation.
- Development of PneumoGAN for pneumonia detection.
- Model training, evaluation, and result visualization.
- Integration of deep learning techniques for robust image classification.

3. Dataset
- Source: Chest X-ray dataset from NIH Clinical Center (https://www.kaggle.com/paultimothymooney/chest-xray-pneumonia)
- Classes: Pneumonia-positive and pneumonia-negative cases
- Input Data: Chest X-ray images in grayscale

4. Technologies Used
- Programming Language: Python
- Libraries:
  - TensorFlow/Keras
  - NumPy
  - Matplotlib
  - scikit-learn
  - OpenCV

5. File Structure
- pneumogan_model.ipynb: Jupyter Notebook with the full implementation of the PneumoGAN model.
- data/: Contains preprocessed datasets (not included in the repository, replace with your dataset).
- results/: Contains generated synthetic images and evaluation metrics.

B. Getting Started

1. Prerequisites
- Python 3.x
- Jupyter Notebook
- Required libraries (install via pip):
  pip install tensorflow keras numpy matplotlib scikit-learn opencv-python

2. Usage
1. Clone this repository:
   git clone https://github.com/vaishakb251/MyProjects.git
2. Navigate to the "PneumoGAN" directory:
   cd MyProjects/PneumoGAN
3. Open the notebook:
   jupyter notebook pneumogan_model.ipynb
4. Replace the data/ directory with your chest X-ray dataset if necessary.
5. Follow the steps in the notebook to train and evaluate the model.

C. Results
PneumoGAN achieved an accuracy of 94.99% on pneumonia detection using chest X-ray images. Generated synthetic samples and detailed evaluation metrics are provided in the results section of the notebook.

D. Acknowledgements
- The Chest X-ray dataset is sourced from the NIH Clinical Center.
- This project highlights the potential of GANs in enhancing medical diagnostics and improving deep learning model performance.
